AK+Everywhere: Make FixedArray OOM-safe FixedArray now doesn\'t expose any infallible constructors anymore. Rather, it exposes fallible methods. Therefore, it can be used for OOM-safe code. This commit also converts the rest of the system to use the new API. However, as an example, VMObject can\'t take advantage of this yet, as we would have to endow VMObject with a fallible static construction method, which would require a very fundamental change to VMObject\'s whole inheritance hierarchy.
